list.name: Default
list.comment: Changed Working of ENNet - Removed parallel processing within networks - Added parallel processing of networks - Removed usage of Procpar, Now using multiprocessing.Pool - Fixed all synapses connecting from source to source - Fixed various outdated interfaces to functions - Updated H&HNeuronSimulatie.py for the new features - Renamed H&HNeuronSimulatie.py to HnHNeuronSimulatie.py - Changed notifications to be uniform. Now in the form of: (class) Message and (class %id) Message - Added various checks to prevent bugs with manual addition of synapses and neurons - Added support for multiple types of synapses and neurons within a network. (This support was dropped and added again) - Now Recorder option 'withTime' is no longer ignored. - Removed Procpar and afflicted code

task.summary:
Changed the workings of ENNet: - Now poolSize = None results in single core execution. This execution method is 1700% faster than Multiprocessing. - Local processing: 100 nodes and 4950 connections for 1 second (dt=0.01ms). 1300 seconds on a 3.8 quad-core i7 first gen.
Innerworkings of Procpar have changed - Loop broken down intro a loop function
